            "date": "2010-02-06 08:38:39", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I would really love to see OSS4 support in the Chrome browser.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "As OSS4 is such a clean design for sound on linux and even other platforms, a support\nfor it should make chrome much easier portable.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Oh, please dont mix the old OSS with the new OSS4.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "As i am a user only, i sadly cant help with patches...", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "but im willing to test it.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "/u/kai.werthwein/", 
            "email": "/u/kai.werthwein/"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2010-02-08 09:28:39", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "For the time being we're sticking with ALSA but have also thought about adding \nPulseAudio support in the future.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I'm no expert at Linux sound APIs but would love to \nhear your thoughts on the topics.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "/u/scherkus@chromium.org/", 
            "email": "/u/scherkus@chromium.org/"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2010-02-08 15:20:10", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I've used OSS, Alsa, PulseAudio, and finally OSS4, and without a doubt OSS4 was the\nmost stable and easiest to setup and use.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "The sound was great, and there wasn't any\nsync issue with video like PulseAudio has.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "The latency of OSS4 is the lowest out of\nthe four I've tried.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "But as of now, I've given up on audio on Linux and bought a Mac.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "/u/takreeger/", 
            "email": "/u/takreeger/"
        }, 
